<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/664840-i-m-about-half-way-through-the-book-and">I&#39;m about half way through the book and I&#39;m surprised. It&#39;s so much of a harder read than Player of Games which was gripping through out. I&#39;m really not liking the way the forward and reverse story lines are interspersed through the book. It makes it very hard to hold my attention. Anyone else have this experience?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_664840'><a id="like_count_community_question_664840" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/664840?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">25 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F12007.Use_of_Weapons">like</a></span>

